headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 34 points and the Phoenix Suns never trailed in a 114-106 victory over the Utah Jazz on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 34, Suns never trail in defeating Jazz 114-106

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 22 points, 17 assists and 10 rebounds, and the Detroit Pistons beat the Toronto Raptors 123-114 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham's triple-double leads Pistons to 123-114 victory over slumping Raptors

headlines.description: — Ja Morant made a tiebreaking jumper with 18 seconds left, Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 33 points and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 127-125 on Saturday night in a game that was tight from start to finish.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant hits tiebreaking shot with 18 seconds left as Grizzlies beat Timberwolves 127-125

events.name: Miami Heat at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro had 32 points, including seven 3-pointers, and the Miami Heat downed the Portland Trail Blazers 119-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro leads Heat with 32 points in a 119-98 win at Portland
